<br>
Exactly.  One thing thats really been bugging me lately is the proliferation of the idea that warriors &quot;shouldn't worry about damage&quot; or &quot;we weren't meant to do damage&quot; and that its &quot;ok&quot; for rogues/monks to do 3x more damage.<br>
<br>
Verant's description of the warrior clearly states that the warrior was designed to &quot;dole out as much punishment as he can take.&quot;  I started a warrior to be both an effective tank and a viable damage dealer.<br>
<br>
Now we are happily regulating ourselves to extra lag on raids when we aren't the ones absorbing the melee damage. <p>Veteran <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=34639>Damacis Bigadanu</a>
