<br>
The non-MT warriors on the raid should be able to do dual wield and do more damage, or use a sick 2-hander, or whatever.  I like the idea of having a choice of being in defensive mode (shield) or offensive mode (no shield).  Just one more thing to do on a raid and one more decision to make.  I don't think you'ld want to use a shield in most exp groups, you don't see hybrids using them in exp groups (not smart ones anyway) either.<br>
<br>
I will aggree that rogs and monks do way to much damage compared to warriors, and I would like to see the dps ratio brought more in line with what they suggested in the melee balancing days  (80/100/120/140)...preferably by bumping warriors and knights damage up a little, rather than nerfing monks and rogues.  But I don't think a shield should permanently replace dual wield, but only in a few situations when you care more about taking damage than dealing it.<br>
<br>
Shields shouldn't effect scalability because only your main tanks should be wearing them. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6629>Brutul Vilesilencer</a><br>

