<br>
... after comparing a drop off one of the easier Velious boss dragons, to the drop off Emperor Ssra. You should have compared to Kreizenns Flame, or Dragon Rib Club for this to be even a remotely useful comparison. Your numbers (which were pretty much a crock anyway) would have come out a bit different.<br>
<br>
Secondly, I dont seem to be able to cast Brells Mountainous Barrier on myself, nor group heal, or use LOH. The spells and abilities you get were the tradeoff for not being able to tank or damage as well as a pure warrior. This change would throw back the BEST equipped warriors in the game to doing at best slightly less damage to a paladin/sk in a guild just breaking into TOV.<br>
<br>
The issue no one seems to be grasping is, even if they balance everything so that warriors can tank better with a shield on, but take a DPS hit.. why then would you need more then 1-3 warriors on ANY raid anywhere? Wouldnt it be a better option for all but the 3 MTs of a guild then to go roll a wizard or monk or rogue? Paladins and SKs already make FAR FAR better add tanks then warriors, being alot more self sustaining and having the ability to hold agro without damaging a mob (very useful in certain places). Improving warriors while nerfing their damage wont help things, even if all other things were equal (which I have zero faith in VI to pull off).<br>
<br>
The stated DPS ratio was knights 80%, warriors 100%, rangers 110%, monks 120% (or was it 130), rogues 140%. As Furor already stated, this chart is a complete joke. Warriors and knights with 2h's are barely different, monks do double the damage of either, rangers with the right AAs also do that and more. And thats not even touching on rogues with 16dam piercers.<br>
<br>
All these problems have stemmed from Verants ridiculous stance on warriors being the BALANCING POST where to start working on other classes without even thinking about touching the &quot;test case&quot;. They balanced, the ratios held true until Luclin AAs+monk weapons+archery mastery+16dam piercers came in. What did warriors get to balance this? One weapon which has +1damage over the previous best.<br>
<br>
I just urge Verant to actually think out the issue before rushing blindly in and @#%$ more things up then alrady are. This current implementation of shields would do just that no matter how much they may add to taunt/defensive skills. <p><a target="new" height=768 width=1024 href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=143620">Zotha Farseer</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bigshow>BigShow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/22/02 8:58:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1109.topic&index=119>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: new on test</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  why do you think there is a serie of spell called furious bash on test?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
